Date: Fri, 20 Aug 1999 11:50:11 PDT
From: Ruth Sponsler <jk55@hotmail.com>

The recent weather in central and South Texas has been dry. Vegetation has
been turning brown and there are few small accumulations of water around.
The milder temperatures and frequent rains that Texas had during June and
early July have given way to hot [95-100Â°F] weather with very little rain
and very high drying potential.
Given these weather conditions, I'll stick my neck out and guess that there
won't be many more cases of dengue in Texas this year.
--
Ruth Sponsler
M.S. Entomology
<jk55@hotmail.com>
